docs.lead_paragraph: The Apalachicola Times contains an account of the capture of the notorious schooner Atwater. She was taken at Cedar Keys by the steamer Spray, of Apalachicola, and carried into the latter port as a prize. She had on board an officer of the United States, with a crew of fifteen men.
